            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03526.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Dec. 13, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. W. H. Hooper,</ab>
            <ab>House of Representatives.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I have received your letter of the 5th instant, with the enclosed draft of a bill to allow writs of error to the Supreme Court of the United States from the Supreme Courts of the Territories.</ab>
            <ab>I do not feel at liberty to express any opinion upon the merits of your proposed bill.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">certain proposed bill.</note>
            
            
            
